TITLE: Handling Form Submission State in TanStack
DESCRIPTION: This code block focuses on preventing invalid forms from being submitted in TanStack Form. It shows how to use the `canSubmit` flag and `form.Subscribe` to conditionally disable the submit button based on the form's validity state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tanstack/form/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/validation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const form = useForm(/* ... */)

return (
  /* ... */

  // Dynamic submit button
  <form.Subscribe
    selector={(state) => [state.canSubmit, state.isSubmitting]}
    children={([canSubmit, isSubmitting]) => (
      <button type="submit" disabled={!canSubmit}>
        {isSubmitting ? '...' : 'Submit'}
      </button>
    )}
  />
)
```

