TITLE: Accessing Field State in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to access a field's state, including its value, validation status, and error messages. It also shows how to check the field's touched, pristine, and dirty states.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tanstack/form/blob/main/docs/framework/react/guides/basic-concepts.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const {
  value,
  meta: { errors, isValidating },
} = field.state

const { isTouched, isPristine, isDirty } = field.state.meta
```

