TITLE: Implementing Form Validation in SolidJS with @tanstack/solid-form
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates both synchronous and asynchronous validation in @tanstack/solid-form. It includes custom validation functions that check for required fields, minimum length, and disallowed content with appropriate error messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tanstack/form/blob/main/docs/framework/solid/guides/basic-concepts.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
<form.Field
  name="firstName"
  validators={{
    onChange: ({ value }) =>
      !value
        ? 'A first name is required'
        : value.length < 3
          ? 'First name must be at least 3 characters'
          : undefined,
    onChangeAsync: async ({ value }) => {
      await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 1000))
      return value.includes('error') && 'No "error" allowed in first name'
    },
  }}
  children={(field) => (
    <>
      <input
        name={field().name}
        value={field().state.value}
        onBlur={field().handleBlur}
        onInput={(e) => field().handleChange(e.target.value)}
      />
      <p>{field().state.meta.errors[0]}</p>
    </>
  )}
/>
```

